    public abstract class AbstractResolver
extends java.lang.Object
implements Resolver, java.beans.PropertyChangeListener
    Default adaptor class for Resovler interface. This abstract class provides the default caching mechanism for positive and negative resolver lookups. It also provides a timeout mechanism to time out lookup results.

    Mark Bednarczyk, Sly Technologies, Inc.

        private int backoff
        Percentage of how many oldest entries to remove from cache.

      • cache

        private java.util.Map<java.lang.Long,java.lang.String> cache
        Main cache map. The timeout is maintaned using a priority queue, that removes timedout entries from this map.

      • cacheCapacity

        private int cacheCapacity
        Just an initial map size.

      • cacheLoadFactor

        private float cacheLoadFactor
        The cache load factor.

      • isModified

        private boolean isModified
        Flag used to mark if any changes have been made to the cache that need to be saved.

      • logger

        protected final java.util.logging.Logger logger
        Logger is supplied from subclass. This allows Abstract logger to log messages attached to actual logger that was intended for

      • maxentries

        private int maxentries
        Hard limit on how many entries can be stored in a cache. When this limit is reached, backoff percentage is used to calculate the number of oldest entries to remove to make room for new entries.

      • mkdirHome

        private boolean mkdirHome
        If set to true, we are allowed to create our resolver home directory, which defaults to jnetpcap home directory.

      • name

        private final java.lang.String name
        Name of this resolver. Same as enum constant name. Used in file names and resolver specific properties.

      • negativeTimeout

        private long negativeTimeout
        When failed to resolve to a name, store the failure information in cache and set the negative hit timeout.

        Resolved to a name.

        The save cache.
